an class=title> Brewing guide</span><hr size=1> Guide to brewing<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 This was written quite a time ago.<br>
<br>
Ok i did it last night...a lot of research material and here it is condensed.<br>
Go to High Hold pass.<br>
Head to the Tigers roar. The pub/inn you have to pass if running thru the zone...its near a narrow bridge and water.<br>
Go into the shop and to the right is Lyn tarburner.<br>
Give her a kiss b'cos she will see a lot of you. She supplies everything you need. Barley, hops, malt and yeasts. These are all you will need at the moment.<br>
When you enter the shop go left and you come to the brew barrel and the bartender. The bartender sells casks. Buy lots after you have filled up with your main components for the drink you are making.<br>
The important thing is to have space before you go to start brewing...sell off your rubbish or leave it in the bank.<br>
Ok I will assume you all have some understanding of combining items etc.<br>
Drink number one is the SHORT BEER.<br>
Recipe is barley +hops +malt +cask. Trivial 31.<br>
Next is MEAD<br>
Recipe is hops +malt + yeasts +cask. Trivial 40.<br>
Next is SHORT ALE<br>
Recipe barley +hops +Flask of water +cask. Trivial 51.<br>
NOTE <br>
Water can be purchased in the shop serpents supplies. Very close to tigers roar, Over little wood bridge, go to left and down ramp to the shop.<br>
next is ALE<br>
Recipe barley +malt + Flask of water +cask. Trivial 68.<br>
<br>
OK there it is...it cost me about 15 PP total and 2 hours game play....I have charisma 120 and intelligence of 155. <br>
After this stage you appear to need purchased components or foraged items...unless you jump to <br>
trivial at 130 OL'TUJIMS FIERCE BREW<br>
Recipe barley+ hops+ yeat+ malt+ cask.<br>
Hmmmm! if you have money to burn!.... i may try it!<br>
To see how long it would take!<br>
<br>
Hope this sheds some light on the brewing skill!<br>
Hic.... oh yes try not to drink too much of your produce!...my alcohol tolerance is now 137.<br>
<br>
